1. Introduction to Strings in PHP

What is a string?

Declaring strings using single quotes ' ' and double quotes " ".
Difference between single and double quotes (variable interpolation, escape sequences)


$name = "Alice";
echo 'Hello $name';   // Output: Hello $name
echo "Hello $name";   // Output: Hello Alice


2. Basic String Functions
Introduce the most commonly used ones with examples:

| Function           | Description                                               | Example                                                         |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `strlen()`         | Returns the length of a string                            | `echo strlen("Hello"); // 5`                                    |
| `str_word_count()` | Counts the number of words                                | `echo str_word_count("Hello world"); // 2`                      |
| `strrev()`         | Reverses a string                                         | `echo strrev("Hello"); // olleH`                                |
| `strpos()`         | Finds the position of the first occurrence of a substring | `echo strpos("Hello world", "world"); // 6`                     |
| `str_replace()`    | Replaces some characters with others                      | `echo str_replace("world", "PHP", "Hello world"); // Hello PHP` |


3. String Manipulation Functions
Show how to transform or modify strings:

strtolower() â†’ converts to lowercase
strtoupper() â†’ converts to uppercase
ucfirst() â†’ capitalizes first letter
ucwords() â†’ capitalizes first letter of each word
trim() â†’ removes whitespace from both sides
ltrim() / rtrim() â†’ remove from left/right side only


$text = "  hello world  ";
echo trim($text);            // "hello world"
echo strtoupper($text);      // "  HELLO WORLD  "
echo ucwords("hello php");   // "Hello Php"



4. Substring and Extraction

substr($string, $start, $length) â€“ extract part of a string
echo substr("Hello world", 0, 5); // Hello


substr_replace($string, $replacement, $start, $length)
echo substr_replace("Hello world", "PHP", 6); // Hello PHP


5. String Comparison

strcmp() â€“ case-sensitive comparison
strcasecmp() â€“ case-insensitive comparison
strnatcmp() â€“ natural order comparison

Example:
echo strcmp("Hello", "hello");   // not equal
echo strcasecmp("Hello", "hello"); // equal


6. String Splitting and Joining

explode() â†’ convert string â†’ array
implode() (or join()) â†’ convert array â†’ string

Example:
$str = "apple,banana,grape";
$fruits = explode(",", $str);
print_r($fruits);
echo implode(" | ", $fruits); // apple | banana | grape


7. Formatting and Escaping

addslashes() / stripslashes()
htmlspecialchars() / htmlentities() for HTML output
printf() / sprintf() for formatted strings

$txt = "I'm a developer";
echo addslashes($txt);  // I\'m a developer
printf("My name is %s and I am %d years old.", "Alice", 25);


